        "text": "As part of my poster on my \"Internationalizing R packages\" poster at useR! 2022, I've created a hosted version of Weblate to demo\/experiment with how to crowd-source translations using a web interface instead of asking for code contributions -- also added all PO files from base R and the suggested packages at <https:\/\/translate.rx.studio> (can suggest translations without registration, but probably better to sign-up).\n\nI'd appreciate any experimentation and feedback (let it be positive or negative), and happy to maintain it under a different domain of that's preferred and this tool looks useful.\n\nFTR the PO files are picked up from the Subversion repo and can be auto-updated (e.g. daily), and happy to create patch files to share back to R Core.",
